To my <normalised orig="louing" auto="true">loving</normalised> and well <lb/>
<normalised orig="beloued" auto="true">beloved</normalised> Parishioners, the Inhabitants <lb/>
of Dicheat in SOMERSETSHIRE, <lb/>
Grace and <lb/>
Peace in Christ <normalised orig="Iesus" auto="true">Jesus</normalised>. <lb/>
                  <lb/>
INstruction of youth <lb/>
is the best seasoner of <lb/>
after ages not <normalised orig="onely" auto="true">only</normalised> <lb/>
for riper knowledge, <lb/>
but also for honest <lb/>
manners. <normalised orig="Wherby" auto="true">Whereby</normalised>, as they brought <lb/>
children to Christ when he was <lb/>
here <normalised orig="conuersant" auto="true">conversant</normalised> on earth, that he <lb/>
should touch them, so may wee <lb/>
bring them to him still, to <normalised orig="blesse" auto="true">bless</normalised> <lb/>
them in turning them from their <lb/>
iniquities, and correcting the <normalised orig="viciousnesse" auto="true">viciousness</normalised> <lb/>
of their first birth, by a <lb/>
new forming <normalised orig="himselfe" auto="true">himself</normalised> in them. <lb/>
For this purpose the Church <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> <lb/>
had at all times <normalised orig="Catechismes" auto="true">Catechisms</normalised>, or <lb/>
<normalised orig="summes" auto="true">sums</normalised> of doctrine concerning <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <fw type="pageNum">A 2</fw>
                  <pb n="1"/>
                  <lb/>
the <normalised orig="chiefe" auto="true">chief</normalised> <normalised orig="poynts" auto="true">points</normalised> of Religion, <lb/>
whereunto they might refer their <lb/>
reading and learning, and (as the <lb/>
Rabbines say) as it were pale in <lb/>
the <normalised orig="generall" auto="true">general</normalised> doctrines that they <lb/>
might not wander in an <normalised orig="endlesse" auto="true">endless</normalised> <lb/>
maze. Answerably here <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> our <lb/>
Church <normalised orig="inioyneth" auto="true">enjoins</normalised> a <normalised orig="forme" auto="true">form</normalised> of <lb/>
doctrine containing the <normalised orig="summe" auto="true">sum</normalised> of <lb/>
the <normalised orig="Couenant" auto="true">Covenant</normalised> of grace, which for <lb/>
memories sake being <normalised orig="inclosed" auto="true">enclosed</normalised> in a <lb/>
very short Epitome; I <normalised orig="haue" auto="true">have</normalised> a little <lb/>
enlarged in a few more Questions <lb/>
and Answers raised out of the <lb/>
same, that you might the better <lb/>
take <normalised orig="vp" auto="true">up</normalised> the Method, and <normalised orig="vnderstand" auto="true">understand</normalised> <lb/>
the Contents thereof. This <lb/>
therefore I propose <normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised> you, as a<lb/>
<normalised orig="loafe" auto="true">loaf</normalised> of wholesome bread broken <lb/>
into more <normalised orig="peeces" auto="true">pieces</normalised>: as a <normalised orig="channell" auto="true">channel</normalised> of <lb/>
<normalised orig="liuing" auto="true">living</normalised> water cut into more streams <lb/>
&amp; <normalised orig="passible" auto="false">passable</normalised> brooks, as a first draught <lb/>
of a picture <normalised orig="portraied" auto="true">portrayed</normalised> out with <lb/>
more particular <normalised orig="coulours" auto="true">colours</normalised> and lineaments, <lb/>
and as a <normalised orig="patterne" auto="true">pattern</normalised> of sound <lb/>
                  <pb n="2"/>
                  <lb/>
doctrine in the <normalised orig="seuerall" auto="true">several</normalised> parts <normalised orig="therof" auto="true">thereof</normalised>. <lb/>
Herein you shall see what the <lb/>
high calling of God is whereunto <lb/>
he <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> called <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised>: with what immunities <lb/>
he <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> enfranchised <normalised orig="vs" auto="true">us</normalised>, <lb/>
what our hopes are of an <normalised orig="immortall" auto="true">immortal</normalised> <lb/>
inheritance, and how we ought <lb/>
to <normalised orig="walke" auto="true">walk</normalised> worthy the same. What <lb/>
then Paul <normalised orig="testifieth" auto="true">testifies</normalised> concerning <normalised orig="Timothie" auto="true">Timothy</normalised> <lb/>
his <normalised orig="sonne" auto="true">son</normalised>, that he had been <lb/>
nourished <normalised orig="vp" auto="true">up</normalised> in the words of faith <lb/>
and good doctrine; the same <normalised orig="doe" auto="true">do</normalised> <lb/>
I desire concerning yours, that together <lb/>
with outward education, <lb/>
you may nourish them <normalised orig="vp" auto="true">up</normalised> in the <lb/>
words of faith and good <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>doct*<normalised orig="ine" auto="true">in</normalised></sic>
                     <corr>doctrine</corr>
                  </choice>: <lb/>
yea, that your <normalised orig="selues" auto="true">selves</normalised> first learning <lb/>
the Principles of the doctrine of <lb/>
Christ, would <normalised orig="goe" auto="true">go</normalised> on <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic><normalised orig="vn" auto="true">un</normalised>*o</sic>
                     <corr><normalised orig="vnto" auto="true">unto</normalised></corr>
                  </choice> perfection,<lb/>
obeying from the heart, <lb/>
the <normalised orig="forme" auto="true">form</normalised> of doctrine which <normalised orig="hath" auto="true">has</normalised> <lb/>
been <normalised orig="deliuered" auto="true">delivered</normalised> you: then I doubt <lb/>
not, your <normalised orig="sonnes" auto="true">sons</normalised> shall grow <normalised orig="vp" auto="true">up</normalised> <normalised orig="vnder" auto="true">under</normalised> <lb/>
you as the plants, your daughters <lb/>
shall be <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>a*</sic>
                     <corr>as</corr>
                  </choice> the polished corners <lb/>
                  <lb/>
                  <fw type="pageNum">A 3</fw>
                  <pb n="3"/>
                  <lb/>
of the Temple; and one and <lb/>
other as good Scribes taught to <lb/>
the <normalised orig="Kingdome" auto="true">Kingdom</normalised> of God. Now the <lb/>
God of all grace make you to <normalised orig="encrease" auto="true">increase</normalised> <lb/>
in knowledge and <normalised orig="iudgement" auto="true">judgment</normalised> <lb/>
to <normalised orig="approue" auto="true">approve</normalised> the best things, <lb/>
and establish your harts <normalised orig="vnblameable" auto="true">unblameable</normalised> <lb/>
in <normalised orig="holines" auto="true">holiness</normalised> before him till the <lb/>
day of Christ. Amen. <lb/>
                  <lb/>
Yours in the Lord <normalised orig="Iesus" auto="true">Jesus</normalised>, <lb/>
in my best <normalised orig="endeauours" auto="true">endeavours</normalised> for <lb/>
your edifying in his <normalised orig="sauing" auto="true">saving</normalised> <lb/>
